description:
## Bug

In tui/src/event.rs handle_slash() for the /! command (~line 1236-1268):

    match tokio::process::Command::new(&argv[0])
        .args(&argv[1..])
        .output()
        .await
    {
        Ok(output) => {
            let raw = String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stdout);
            // ... truncate and send
        }
        Err(e) => { /* spawn error */ }
    }

Only output.stdout is captured and sent to chat. output.stderr is ignored entirely. The command's exit status (output.status) is also not checked.

## Impact

When a command fails and writes its error message to stderr (e.g., 'ls /nonexistent', 'grep invalid-regex'), the user sees nothing in the chat — no output, no indication of failure. This is misleading: the user cannot tell whether the command succeeded silently or failed.

## Fix

After capturing output, check output.status.success(). If it failed, include a system message in the chat showing the exit code and/or stderr content (truncated).
